<h3>Open Questions</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Is <code>oldValue</code> always carried on the record? Is <code>version</code> a Lamport clock, a vector clock, or an opaque token? Where exactly is the CRDT-op adapter boundary?</li>
    <li>What is the <code>ChangeSource</code> channel set, and should the standard adopt CloudEvents envelope fields? Is trace linkage mandatory or optional?</li>
    <li>Sync vs microtask-batched vs scheduled delivery of records — does the protocol take a position or make it configurable?</li>
    <li>Do any production systems implement a canonical-change-record normalization bridging signals → JSON Patch → CRDT? (The interop core remains synthesis, not a verified fact.)</li>
    <li>Operational Transformation vs op-based CRDTs for concurrent-edit ordering — transport and memory tradeoffs in practice.</li>
</ul>
